  <!-- ═══════ ABOUT / POSITIONING ═══════ -->
  <section id="about">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-label"><span class="label-line"></span>Who I Am</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Designing Games<br><em>From the Inside Out</em></h2>
      <p class="about-intro reveal">
        I've spent nearly a decade inside games — not just playing them, but dissecting them.
        I started in QA, watching players find every exploit I failed to predict.
        Moved into Operations, learning that a great design means nothing if the live
        environment can't sustain it. Then into Live-Ops Design, Game Design, and eventually
        Product Ownership.<br><br>
        This journey gave me something rare: <strong>the ability to design systems that
        don't just look good on paper — they survive real players, real economies,
        and real deadlines.</strong>
      </p>

      <div class="value-cards">
        <div class="value-card reveal">
          <div class="value-icon">⚙️</div>
          <h3>Systems Thinker</h3>
          <p>I design interconnected gameplay mechanics — quests, skills, economy, combat — that scale and evolve with the player base.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.1s">
          <div class="value-icon">📊</div>
          <h3>Data-Shaped</h3>
          <p>From QA to Analytics to Live-Ops, every design decision I make is informed by real player behavior and measurable outcomes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card reveal" style="transition-delay:0.2s">
          <div class="value-icon">🎯</div>
          <h3>Product-Minded</h3>
          <p>I don't just design features. I own the product vision — from concept to launch to post-launch tuning.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════ FEATURED PROJECTS ═══════ -->
